Duduzane Zuma is back at the State Capture
Commission of Inquiry. On Monday, former president Jacob
Zuma’s son denied former deputy finance minister Mcebisi Jonas’ claim
that he was present went the Gupta brothers allegedly offered Jonas R600
million to take the position of finance minister in 2015. He told the commission that he held various meetings at the
Gupta compound in Saxonwold, but none of them were corrupt.